Driver’s Handbook | 113
 ▶ Variations in roadway width;
 ▶ Zones reserved for buses and other heavy vehicles;
 ▶ Edges of intersections;
 ▶ Stop lines;
 ▶ Pedestrian, school and playground crosswalks;
 ▶ Parking areas;
 ▶ Commercial service areas;
 ▶ Special manoeuvres as indicated by arrows;
 ▶ Obstructions on or next to the road ahead;
 ▶ Reversible lanes;
 ▶ Bikeways;
 ▶ Reserved lanes;
 ▶ Two-way left-turn lanes;
 ▶ Runaway lanes.
Colour of pavement markings
Two colours, yellow and white, are used to differentiate the function 
of pavement markings.
Yellow markings:
 ▶ Separate traffic lanes in opposite directions;
 ▶ Indicate the left side of the road on divided roadways,  highways  
and one-way roadways;
 ▶ Indicate the left edge of a ramp on highways;
 ▶ Indicate areas where parking is prohibited;

